## 📖 Overview

A booking platform built to handle the hardest part of event ticketing: **preventing double-booked seats** when many users compete for the same inventory at the same time — while keeping payments reliable and auditable.

## ✨ Key Features

- 🪑 **Real-time live seat reservation** — seat status updates instantly across all connected clients via WebSockets
- 🔒 **Database-level locking** on the Spring Boot core to guarantee no two users can reserve the same seat simultaneously, even under concurrent load
- 💳 **Dedicated payment microservice** built in Node.js, integrated with Razorpay, kept isolated from the core booking logic for security and fault tolerance
- 📊 Organizer dashboard for managing events, ticket tiers, and sales
- 🔔 Live booking status via Socket.IO — no manual refresh needed

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
┌────────────┐      WebSocket (live seats)     ┌──────────────────┐
│   React    │ ◄─────────────────────────────► │  Spring Boot Core │
│  Frontend  │                                  │  (bookings, DB    │
└─────┬──────┘                                  │   locks, seats)   │
      │                                          └─────────┬─────────┘
      │            REST (checkout)                         │
      ▼                                                     ▼
┌──────────────────┐   webhook confirm    ┌──────────────────────┐
│  Node.js Payment  │ ───────────────────► │      PostgreSQL       │
│  Microservice      │                      │  (bookings, seats,    │
│  (Razorpay)         │                     │   payments)            │
└──────────────────┘                       └──────────────────────┘
```

## 🧰 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React |
| Core Backend | Spring Boot |
| Payment Service | Node.js + Razorpay |
| Real-time | Socket.IO / WebSockets |
| Database | PostgreSQL |

## 🚀 Getting Started

```bash
git clone https://github.com/hackerstudent29/Event-Management-System-main.git
cd Event-Management-System-main

# Spring Boot core
cd backend
./mvnw spring-boot:run

# Payment microservice
cd ../payment-service
npm install
npm start

# Frontend
cd ../frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Configure environment variables for PostgreSQL connection and Razorpay keys in `application.properties` and `.env` respectively.

